li.source:
public class SomeClass
{
    public void someMethod()
    {
        if (xxx)
        {
        }
    }
}

for (Iterator stereotypeIterator = stereotypes.iterator(); stereotypeIterator.hasNext();)
{
    ModelElement stereotype = (ModelElement)stereotypeIterator.next();
    stereoTypeNames.add(stereotype.getName());
}

public int getEntityCount()
{
    // don't do this:
    /*
        if (condition)
        {
           return 6;
        }
        return 0;
    */

    // but do this:
    int entityCount = 0;

    if (condition)
    {
        entityCount = 6;
    }

    return entityCount;
}

ul.li:
                        Instance Variables: Instance variables should not have any
                        prefix and must be referenced using the this object. Example :

public class SomeClass
{
    private String someString;
    ...
    public void someMethod()
    {
        logger.debug("Value = " + this.someString);
    }
}

                        Parameter Names: Method parameters should not have any
                        prefix. For example :

public void someMethod(String className)
{
}

li.source:
try
{
   ...
}
catch (Exception ex)
{
    logger.error("Some error has occurred" + ex);
}

try
{
   ...
}
catch (Exception ex)
{
    logger.error("Some error has occurred" + ex);
    ExceptionRecorder.instance().record( ex );
}
